112 void EncCu::setUpLambda (Slice& slice, const double dLambda, const int iQP, const bool setSliceLambda, const bool saveUnadjusted)
113 {
114  // store lambda
115  m_cRdCost.setLambda( dLambda, slice.sps->bitDepths );
116 
117  // for RDO
118  // in RdCost there is only one lambda because the luma and chroma bits are not separated, instead we weight the distortion of chroma.
119  double dLambdas[MAX_NUM_COMP] = { dLambda };
120  for( uint32_t compIdx = 1; compIdx < MAX_NUM_COMP; compIdx++ )
121  {
122  const ComponentID compID = ComponentID( compIdx );
123  int chromaQPOffset = slice.pps->chromaQpOffset[compID] + slice.sliceChromaQpDelta[ compID ];
124  int qpc = slice.sps->chromaQpMappingTable.getMappedChromaQpValue(compID, iQP) + chromaQPOffset;
125  double tmpWeight = pow( 2.0, ( iQP - qpc ) / 3.0 ); // takes into account of the chroma qp mapping and chroma qp Offset
126  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_DepQuantEnabled/* && !( m_pcEncCfg->getLFNST() ) */)
127  {
128  tmpWeight *= ( m_pcEncCfg->m_GOPSize >= 8 ? pow( 2.0, 0.1/3.0 ) : pow( 2.0, 0.2/3.0 ) ); // increase chroma weight for dependent quantization (in order to reduce bit rate shift from chroma to luma)
129  }
130  m_cRdCost.setDistortionWeight( compID, tmpWeight );
131  dLambdas[compIdx] = dLambda / tmpWeight;
132  }
133 
134  // for RDOQ
135  m_cTrQuant.setLambdas( dLambdas );
136 
137  // for SAO, ALF
138  if (setSliceLambda)
139  {
140  slice.setLambdas( dLambdas );
141  }
142  if( saveUnadjusted )
143  {
144  m_cRdCost.saveUnadjustedLambda();
145  }
146 }
147 
148 void EncCu::updateLambda(const Slice& slice, const double ctuLambda, const int ctuQP, const int newQP, const bool saveUnadjusted)
149 {
150  const double corrFactor = pow (2.0, double (newQP - ctuQP) / 3.0);
151  const double newLambda = ctuLambda * corrFactor;
152  const double* oldLambdas = slice.getLambdas(); // assumes prior setUpLambda (slice, ctuLambda) call!
153  const double newLambdas[MAX_NUM_COMP] = { oldLambdas[COMP_Y] * corrFactor, oldLambdas[COMP_Cb] * corrFactor, oldLambdas[COMP_Cr] * corrFactor };
154 
155  m_cTrQuant.setLambdas ( newLambdas);
156  m_cRdCost.setLambda ( newLambda, slice.sps->bitDepths);
157 
158  if (saveUnadjusted)
159  {
160  m_cRdCost.saveUnadjustedLambda(); // TODO hlm: check if this actually improves the overall quality
161  }
162 }

164 void EncCu::init( const VVEncCfg& encCfg, const SPS& sps, std::vector<int>* const globalCtuQpVector, Ctx* syncPicCtx, RateCtrl* pRateCtrl )
165 {
166  DecCu::init( &m_cTrQuant, &m_cIntraSearch, &m_cInterSearch, encCfg.m_internChromaFormat );
167  m_cRdCost.create ();
168  m_cRdCost.setCostMode( encCfg.m_costMode );
169  if ( encCfg.m_lumaReshapeEnable || encCfg.m_lumaLevelToDeltaQPEnabled )
170  {
171  m_cRdCost.setReshapeInfo( encCfg.m_lumaReshapeEnable ? encCfg.m_reshapeSignalType : RESHAPE_SIGNAL_PQ, encCfg.m_internalBitDepth[ CH_L ], encCfg.m_internChromaFormat );
172  }
173 
174  m_modeCtrl.init ( encCfg, &m_cRdCost );
175  m_cIntraSearch.init ( encCfg, &m_cTrQuant, &m_cRdCost, &m_SortedPelUnitBufs, m_unitCache );
176  m_cInterSearch.init ( encCfg, &m_cTrQuant, &m_cRdCost, &m_modeCtrl, m_cIntraSearch.getSaveCSBuf() );
177  m_cTrQuant.init ( nullptr, encCfg.m_RDOQ, encCfg.m_useRDOQTS, encCfg.m_useSelectiveRDOQ, false, true, false /*m_useTransformSkipFast*/, encCfg.m_quantThresholdVal );
178 
179  m_syncPicCtx = syncPicCtx;
180  m_pcRateCtrl = pRateCtrl;
181 
182  m_rcMutex = (encCfg.m_numThreads > 0) ? &m_pcRateCtrl->rcMutex : nullptr;
183 
184  // Initialise scaling lists: The encoder will only use the SPS scaling lists. The PPS will never be marked present.
185  const int maxLog2TrDynamicRange[ MAX_NUM_CH ] = { sps.getMaxLog2TrDynamicRange( CH_L ), sps.getMaxLog2TrDynamicRange( CH_C ) };
186  m_cTrQuant.getQuant()->setFlatScalingList( maxLog2TrDynamicRange, sps.bitDepths );
187 
188  m_pcEncCfg = &encCfg;
189 
190  m_GeoCostList.init(GEO_NUM_PARTITION_MODE, encCfg.m_maxNumGeoCand );
191  m_AFFBestSATDCost = MAX_DOUBLE;
192 
193  unsigned uiMaxSize = encCfg.m_CTUSize;
194  ChromaFormat chromaFormat = encCfg.m_internChromaFormat;
195 
196  Area ctuArea = Area( 0, 0, uiMaxSize, uiMaxSize );
197 
198  for( int i = 0; i < maxCuDepth; i++ )
199  {
200  Area area = Area( 0, 0, uiMaxSize >> ( i >> 1 ), uiMaxSize >> ( ( i + 1 ) >> 1 ) );
201 
202  if( area.width < (1 << MIN_CU_LOG2) || area.height < (1 << MIN_CU_LOG2) )
203  {
204  m_pTempCS[i] = m_pBestCS[i] = nullptr;
205  continue;
206  }
207 
208  m_pTempCS[i] = new CodingStructure( m_unitCache, nullptr );
209  m_pBestCS[i] = new CodingStructure( m_unitCache, nullptr );
210 
211  m_pTempCS[i]->create( chromaFormat, area, false );
212  m_pBestCS[i]->create( chromaFormat, area, false );
213 
214  m_pOrgBuffer[i].create( chromaFormat, area );
215  m_pRspBuffer[i].create( CHROMA_400, area );
216  }
217 
218  m_pTempCS2 = new CodingStructure( m_unitCache, nullptr );
219  m_pBestCS2 = new CodingStructure( m_unitCache, nullptr );
220 
221  m_pTempCS2->create( chromaFormat, ctuArea, false );
222  m_pBestCS2->create( chromaFormat, ctuArea, false );
223 
224  m_cuChromaQpOffsetIdxPlus1 = 0;
225  m_tempQpDiff = 0;
226  m_globalCtuQpVector = globalCtuQpVector;
227 
228  m_SortedPelUnitBufs.create( chromaFormat, uiMaxSize, uiMaxSize );
229 
230  for( uint8_t i = 0; i < MAX_TMP_BUFS; i++)
231  {
232  m_aTmpStorageLCU[i].create(chromaFormat, Area(0, 0, uiMaxSize, uiMaxSize));
233  }
234  for (unsigned ui = 0; ui < MRG_MAX_NUM_CANDS; ui++)
235  {
236  m_acMergeTmpBuffer[ui].create(chromaFormat, Area(0, 0, uiMaxSize, uiMaxSize));
237  }
238 
239 
240  const unsigned maxDepth = 2 * MAX_CU_SIZE_IDX;
241  m_CtxBuffer.resize( maxDepth );
242  m_CurrCtx = 0;
243  if( encCfg.m_EDO )
244  m_dbBuffer.create( chromaFormat, Area( 0, 0, uiMaxSize, uiMaxSize ), 0, 8 );
245 }

248 void EncCu::destroy()
249 {
250  for( int i = 0; i < maxCuDepth; i++ )
251  {
252  if( m_pTempCS[i] )
253  {
254  m_pTempCS[i]->destroy();
255  delete m_pTempCS[i]; m_pTempCS[i] = nullptr;
256  }
257 
258  if( m_pBestCS[i] )
259  {
260  m_pBestCS[i]->destroy();
261  delete m_pBestCS[i]; m_pBestCS[i] = nullptr;
262  }
263 
264  m_pOrgBuffer[i].destroy();
265  m_pRspBuffer[i].destroy();
266  }
267 
268  m_pTempCS2->destroy();
269  m_pBestCS2->destroy();
270 
271  delete m_pTempCS2; m_pTempCS2 = nullptr;
272  delete m_pBestCS2; m_pBestCS2 = nullptr;
273 
274  m_SortedPelUnitBufs.destroy();
275 
276  for( uint8_t i = 0; i < MAX_TMP_BUFS; i++)
277  {
278  m_aTmpStorageLCU[i].destroy();
279  }
280  for (unsigned ui = 0; ui < MRG_MAX_NUM_CANDS; ui++)
281  {
282  m_acMergeTmpBuffer[ui].destroy();
283  }
284 
285 
286  m_dbBuffer.destroy();
287 }

299 void EncCu::encodeCtu( Picture* pic, int (&prevQP)[MAX_NUM_CH], uint32_t ctuXPosInCtus, uint32_t ctuYPosInCtus )
300 {
301  CodingStructure& cs = *pic->cs; //taabane
302  Slice* slice = cs.slice;
303  const PreCalcValues& pcv = *cs.pcv;
304  const uint32_t widthInCtus = pcv.widthInCtus;
305 
306 #if ENABLE_MEASURE_SEARCH_SPACE
307  if( ctuXPosInCtus == 0 && ctuYPosInCtus == 0 )
308  {
309  g_searchSpaceAcc.picW = pic->lwidth();
310  g_searchSpaceAcc.picH = pic->lheight();
311  g_searchSpaceAcc.addSlice( slice->isIntra(), slice->depth );
312  }
313 
314 #endif
315  const int ctuRsAddr = ctuYPosInCtus * pcv.widthInCtus + ctuXPosInCtus;
316  const uint32_t firstCtuRsAddrOfTile = 0;
317  const uint32_t tileXPosInCtus = firstCtuRsAddrOfTile % widthInCtus;
318 
319  const Position pos (ctuXPosInCtus * pcv.maxCUSize, ctuYPosInCtus * pcv.maxCUSize);
320  const UnitArea ctuArea( cs.area.chromaFormat, Area( pos.x, pos.y, pcv.maxCUSize, pcv.maxCUSize ) );
321  DTRACE_UPDATE( g_trace_ctx, std::make_pair( "ctu", ctuRsAddr ) );
322 
323  if ((cs.slice->sliceType != VVENC_I_SLICE || cs.sps->IBC) && ctuXPosInCtus == tileXPosInCtus)
324  {
325  cs.motionLutBuf[ctuYPosInCtus].lut.resize(0);
326  cs.motionLutBuf[ctuYPosInCtus].lutIbc.resize(0);
327  }
328 
329  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_ensureWppBitEqual && ctuXPosInCtus == 0 )
330  {
331  if( ctuYPosInCtus > 0 )
332  {
333  m_CABACEstimator->initCtxModels( *slice );
334  }
335 
336  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_entropyCodingSyncEnabled && ctuYPosInCtus )
337  {
338  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_syncPicCtx[ctuYPosInCtus-1];
339  }
340 
341  prevQP[CH_L] = prevQP[CH_C] = slice->sliceQp; // hlm: call CU::predictQP() here!
342  }
343  else if (ctuRsAddr == firstCtuRsAddrOfTile )
344  {
345  m_CABACEstimator->initCtxModels( *slice );
346  prevQP[CH_L] = prevQP[CH_C] = slice->sliceQp; // hlm: call CU::predictQP() here!
347  }
348  else if (ctuXPosInCtus == tileXPosInCtus && m_pcEncCfg->m_entropyCodingSyncEnabled)
349  {
350  // reset and then update contexts to the state at the end of the top-right CTU (if within current slice and tile).
351  m_CABACEstimator->initCtxModels( *slice );
352 
353  if( cs.getCURestricted( pos.offset(0, -1), pos, slice->independentSliceIdx, 0, CH_L, TREE_D ) )
354  {
355  // Top-right is available, we use it.
356  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_syncPicCtx[ctuYPosInCtus-1];
357  }
358  prevQP[CH_L] = prevQP[CH_C] = slice->sliceQp; // hlm: call CU::predictQP() here!
359  }
360 
361  xCompressCtu( cs, ctuArea, ctuRsAddr, prevQP );
362 
363  m_CABACEstimator->resetBits();
364  m_CABACEstimator->coding_tree_unit( cs, ctuArea, prevQP, ctuRsAddr, true, true );
365 
366  // Store probabilities of second CTU in line into buffer - used only if wavefront-parallel-processing is enabled.
367  if( ctuXPosInCtus == tileXPosInCtus && m_pcEncCfg->m_entropyCodingSyncEnabled )
368  {
369  m_syncPicCtx[ctuYPosInCtus] = m_CABACEstimator->getCtx();
370  }
371 
372  const int numberOfWrittenBits = int( m_CABACEstimator->getEstFracBits() >> SCALE_BITS );
373  xUpdateAfterCtuRC( slice, numberOfWrittenBits, ctuRsAddr );
374 }

380 void EncCu::xCompressCtu( CodingStructure& cs, const UnitArea& area, const unsigned ctuRsAddr, const int prevQP[] )
381 {
382  m_modeCtrl.initCTUEncoding( *cs.slice );
383 
384  // init the partitioning manager
385  Partitioner *partitioner = &m_partitioner;
386  partitioner->initCtu( area, CH_L, *cs.slice );
387 
388  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_IBCMode )
389  {
390  m_cInterSearch.resetCtuRecordIBC();
391  }
392 
393  // init current context pointer
394  m_CurrCtx = m_CtxBuffer.data();
395 
396  PelStorage* orgBuffer = &m_pOrgBuffer[0];
397  PelStorage* rspBuffer = &m_pRspBuffer[0];
398  CodingStructure *tempCS = m_pTempCS [0];
399  CodingStructure *bestCS = m_pBestCS [0];
400  cs.initSubStructure( *tempCS, partitioner->chType, partitioner->currArea(), false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
401  cs.initSubStructure( *bestCS, partitioner->chType, partitioner->currArea(), false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
402  m_CABACEstimator->determineNeighborCus( *tempCS, partitioner->currArea(), partitioner->chType, partitioner->treeType );
403 
404  // copy the relevant area
405  UnitArea clippedArea = clipArea( partitioner->currArea(), cs.area );
406  CPelUnitBuf org = cs.picture->getFilteredOrigBuffer().valid() ? cs.picture->getRspOrigBuf( clippedArea ) : cs.picture->getOrigBuf( clippedArea );
407  tempCS->getOrgBuf( clippedArea ).copyFrom( org );
408  const ReshapeData& reshapeData = cs.picture->reshapeData;
409  if( cs.slice->lmcsEnabled && reshapeData.getCTUFlag() )
410  {
411  tempCS->getRspOrgBuf( clippedArea.Y() ).rspSignal( org.get( COMP_Y) , reshapeData.getFwdLUT() );
412  }
413 
414  tempCS->currQP[CH_L] = bestCS->currQP[CH_L] =
415  tempCS->baseQP = bestCS->baseQP = cs.slice->sliceQp;
416  tempCS->prevQP[CH_L] = bestCS->prevQP[CH_L] = prevQP[CH_L];
417 
418  xCompressCU( tempCS, bestCS, *partitioner );
419  // all signals were already copied during compression if the CTU was split - at this point only the structures are copied to the top level CS
420 
421  // Ensure that a coding was found
422  // Selected mode's RD-cost must be not MAX_DOUBLE.
423  CHECK( bestCS->cus.empty() , "No possible encoding found" );
424  CHECK( bestCS->cus[0]->predMode == NUMBER_OF_PREDICTION_MODES, "No possible encoding found" );
425  CHECK( bestCS->cost == MAX_DOUBLE , "No possible encoding found" );
426 
427  if ( m_wppMutex ) m_wppMutex->lock();
428 
429  cs.useSubStructure( *bestCS, partitioner->chType, TREE_D, CS::getArea( *bestCS, area, partitioner->chType, partitioner->treeType ), true );
430 
431  if ( m_wppMutex ) m_wppMutex->unlock();
432 
433  if( CS::isDualITree( cs ) && isChromaEnabled( cs.pcv->chrFormat ) )
434  {
435  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_CurrCtx->start;
436 
437  partitioner->initCtu( area, CH_C, *cs.slice );
438 
439  cs.initSubStructure( *tempCS, partitioner->chType, partitioner->currArea(), false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
440  cs.initSubStructure( *bestCS, partitioner->chType, partitioner->currArea(), false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
441  m_CABACEstimator->determineNeighborCus( *tempCS, partitioner->currArea(), partitioner->chType, partitioner->treeType );
442  tempCS->currQP[CH_C] = bestCS->currQP[CH_C] =
443  tempCS->baseQP = bestCS->baseQP = cs.slice->sliceQp;
444  tempCS->prevQP[CH_C] = bestCS->prevQP[CH_C] = prevQP[CH_C];
445 
446  xCompressCU( tempCS, bestCS, *partitioner );
447 
448  // Ensure that a coding was found
449  // Selected mode's RD-cost must be not MAX_DOUBLE.
450  CHECK( bestCS->cus.empty() , "No possible encoding found" );
451  CHECK( bestCS->cus[0]->predMode == NUMBER_OF_PREDICTION_MODES, "No possible encoding found" );
452  CHECK( bestCS->cost == MAX_DOUBLE , "No possible encoding found" );
453 
454  if ( m_wppMutex ) m_wppMutex->lock();
455 
456  cs.useSubStructure( *bestCS, partitioner->chType, TREE_D, CS::getArea( *bestCS, area, partitioner->chType, partitioner->treeType ), true );
457 
458  if ( m_wppMutex ) m_wppMutex->unlock();
459  }
460 
461  if ( m_pcEncCfg->m_RCTargetBitrate > 0 )
462  {
463  cs.slice->pic->encRCPic->lcu[ ctuRsAddr ].actualMSE = (double)bestCS->dist / (double)cs.slice->pic->encRCPic->lcu[ ctuRsAddr ].numberOfPixel;
464  }
465 
466  // reset context states and uninit context pointer
467  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_CurrCtx->start;
468  m_CurrCtx = 0;
469 }

473 bool EncCu::xCheckBestMode( CodingStructure *&tempCS, CodingStructure *&bestCS, Partitioner &partitioner, const EncTestMode& encTestMode, const bool useEDO )
474 {
475  bool bestCSUpdated = false;
476 
477  if( !tempCS->cus.empty() )
478  {
479  if( tempCS->cus.size() == 1 )
480  {
481  const CodingUnit& cu = *tempCS->cus.front();
482  CHECK( cu.skip && !cu.mergeFlag, "Skip flag without a merge flag is not allowed!" );
483  }
484 
485  DTRACE_BEST_MODE( tempCS, bestCS, m_cRdCost.getLambda(true), useEDO );
486 
487  if( m_modeCtrl.useModeResult( encTestMode, tempCS, partitioner, useEDO ) )
488  {
489  std::swap( tempCS, bestCS );
490  // store temp best CI for next CU coding
491  m_CurrCtx->best = m_CABACEstimator->getCtx();
492  bestCSUpdated = true;
493  }
494  }
495 
496  // reset context states
497  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_CurrCtx->start;
498  return bestCSUpdated;
499 
500 }

502 void EncCu::xCompressCU( CodingStructure*& tempCS, CodingStructure*& bestCS, Partitioner& partitioner )
503 {
504  PROFILER_SCOPE_AND_STAGE_EXT( 1, g_timeProfiler, P_COMPRESS_CU, tempCS, partitioner.chType );
505  const Area& lumaArea = tempCS->area.Y();
506 
507  Slice& slice = *tempCS->slice;
508  const PPS &pps = *tempCS->pps;
509  const SPS &sps = *tempCS->sps;
510  const uint32_t uiLPelX = tempCS->area.Y().lumaPos().x;
511  const uint32_t uiTPelY = tempCS->area.Y().lumaPos().y;
512 
513  m_modeCtrl.initBlk( tempCS->area, slice.pic->poc );
514 
515  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_usePerceptQPA && pps.useDQP && isLuma (partitioner.chType) && partitioner.currQgEnable())
516  {
517  const PreCalcValues &pcv = *pps.pcv;
518  Picture* const pic = bestCS->picture;
519  const uint32_t ctuRsAddr = getCtuAddr (partitioner.currQgPos, pcv);
520  const bool rateCtrlFrame = m_pcEncCfg->m_RCTargetBitrate > 0;
521 
522  if (partitioner.currSubdiv == 0) // CTU-level QP adaptation
523  {
524  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_usePerceptQPATempFiltISlice == 2) || rateCtrlFrame)
525  {
526  if (rateCtrlFrame)
527  {
528  // frame-level or GOP-level RC + QPA
529  pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ ctuRsAddr ] += pic->encRCPic->picQPOffsetQPA;
530  pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ ctuRsAddr ] = Clip3( 0, MAX_QP, (int)pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ ctuRsAddr ] );
531  pic->ctuQpaLambda[ ctuRsAddr ] *= pic->encRCPic->picLambdaOffsetQPA;
532  pic->ctuQpaLambda[ ctuRsAddr ] = Clip3( m_pcRateCtrl->encRCGOP->minEstLambda, m_pcRateCtrl->encRCGOP->maxEstLambda, pic->ctuQpaLambda[ ctuRsAddr ] );
533  }
534  m_tempQpDiff = pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ctuRsAddr] - BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, lumaArea );
535  }
536 
537  if ((!slice.isIntra() || slice.sps->IBC) && // Museum fix
538  (uiLPelX + (pcv.maxCUSize >> 1) < (m_pcEncCfg->m_PadSourceWidth)) &&
539  (uiTPelY + (pcv.maxCUSize >> 1) < (m_pcEncCfg->m_PadSourceHeight)))
540  {
541  const uint32_t h = lumaArea.height >> 1;
542  const uint32_t w = lumaArea.width >> 1;
543  const int adQPTL = BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, Area (uiLPelX + 0, uiTPelY + 0, w, h));
544  const int adQPTR = BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, Area (uiLPelX + w, uiTPelY + 0, w, h));
545  const int adQPBL = BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, Area (uiLPelX + 0, uiTPelY + h, w, h));
546  const int adQPBR = BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, Area (uiLPelX + w, uiTPelY + h, w, h));
547 
548  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP =
549  bestCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->baseQP = std::min (std::min (adQPTL, adQPTR), std::min (adQPBL, adQPBR));
550  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_usePerceptQPATempFiltISlice == 2) || rateCtrlFrame)
551  {
552  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_usePerceptQPATempFiltISlice == 2) && (m_globalCtuQpVector->size() > ctuRsAddr) && (slice.TLayer == 0) // last CTU row of non-Intra key-frame
553  && (m_pcEncCfg->m_IntraPeriod == 2 * m_pcEncCfg->m_GOPSize) && (ctuRsAddr >= pcv.widthInCtus) && (uiTPelY + pcv.maxCUSize > m_pcEncCfg->m_PadSourceHeight))
554  {
555  m_globalCtuQpVector->at (ctuRsAddr) = m_globalCtuQpVector->at (ctuRsAddr - pcv.widthInCtus); // copy the pumping reducing QP offset from the top CTU neighbor
556  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP =
557  bestCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->baseQP = tempCS->baseQP - m_globalCtuQpVector->at (ctuRsAddr);
558  }
559  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP =
560  bestCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->baseQP = Clip3 (0, MAX_QP, tempCS->baseQP + m_tempQpDiff);
561  }
562  }
563  else
564  {
565  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP =
566  bestCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->baseQP = pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ctuRsAddr];
567  }
568  setUpLambda ( slice, pic->ctuQpaLambda[ctuRsAddr], pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ctuRsAddr], false, true );
569  }
570  else if (slice.isIntra() && !slice.sps->IBC) // sub-CTU QPA
571  {
572  CHECK ((partitioner.currArea().lwidth() >= pcv.maxCUSize) || (partitioner.currArea().lheight() >= pcv.maxCUSize), "sub-CTU delta-QP error");
573  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP = BitAllocation::applyQPAdaptationSubCtu (&slice, m_pcEncCfg, lumaArea);
574 
575  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_usePerceptQPATempFiltISlice == 2) || rateCtrlFrame)
576  {
577  tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] = tempCS->baseQP = Clip3 (0, MAX_QP, tempCS->baseQP + m_tempQpDiff);
578  }
579 
580  updateLambda (slice, pic->ctuQpaLambda[ctuRsAddr], pic->ctuAdaptedQP[ctuRsAddr], tempCS->baseQP, true );
581  }
582  }
583 
584  m_modeCtrl.initCULevel( partitioner, *tempCS );
585  m_sbtCostSave[0] = m_sbtCostSave[1] = MAX_DOUBLE;
586 
587  m_CurrCtx->start = m_CABACEstimator->getCtx();
588 
589  m_cuChromaQpOffsetIdxPlus1 = 0;
590 
591  if( slice.chromaQpAdjEnabled )
592  {
593  // TODO M0133 : double check encoder decisions with respect to chroma QG detection and actual encode
594  int lgMinCuSize = sps.log2MinCodingBlockSize +
595  std::max<int>(0, floorLog2(sps.CTUSize - sps.log2MinCodingBlockSize - int((slice.isIntra() ? slice.picHeader->cuChromaQpOffsetSubdivIntra : slice.picHeader->cuChromaQpOffsetSubdivInter) / 2)));
596  if( partitioner.currQgChromaEnable() )
597  {
598  m_cuChromaQpOffsetIdxPlus1 = ( ( uiLPelX >> lgMinCuSize ) + ( uiTPelY >> lgMinCuSize ) ) % ( pps.chromaQpOffsetListLen + 1 );
599  }
600  }
601 
602  DTRACE_UPDATE( g_trace_ctx, std::make_pair( "cux", uiLPelX ) );
603  DTRACE_UPDATE( g_trace_ctx, std::make_pair( "cuy", uiTPelY ) );
604  DTRACE_UPDATE( g_trace_ctx, std::make_pair( "cuw", tempCS->area.lwidth() ) );
605  DTRACE_UPDATE( g_trace_ctx, std::make_pair( "cuh", tempCS->area.lheight() ) );
606  DTRACE( g_trace_ctx, D_COMMON, "@(%4d,%4d) [%2dx%2d]\n", tempCS->area.lx(), tempCS->area.ly(), tempCS->area.lwidth(), tempCS->area.lheight() );
607 
608  if( tempCS->slice->checkLDC )
609  {
610  m_bestBcwCost[0] = m_bestBcwCost[1] = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
611  m_bestBcwIdx[0] = m_bestBcwIdx[1] = -1;
612  }
613 
614  m_cInterSearch.resetSavedAffineMotion();
615  {
616  const ComprCUCtx &cuECtx = *m_modeCtrl.comprCUCtx;
617  const CodingStructure& cs = *tempCS;
618  const PartSplit implicitSplit = partitioner.getImplicitSplit( cs );
619  const bool isBoundary = implicitSplit != CU_DONT_SPLIT;
620  const bool lossless = false;
621  int qp = cs.baseQP;
622 
623 #if ENABLE_MEASURE_SEARCH_SPACE
624  if( !isBoundary )
625  {
626  g_searchSpaceAcc.addPartition( partitioner.currArea(), partitioner.isSepTree( *tempCS ) ? partitioner.chType : MAX_NUM_CH );
627  }
628 
629 #endif
630  if( ! isBoundary )
631  {
632  if (pps.useDQP && partitioner.isSepTree (*tempCS) && isChroma (partitioner.chType))
633  {
634  const ChromaFormat chromaFm = tempCS->area.chromaFormat;
635  const Position chromaCentral (tempCS->area.Cb().chromaPos().offset (tempCS->area.Cb().chromaSize().width >> 1, tempCS->area.Cb().chromaSize().height >> 1));
636  const Position lumaRefPos (chromaCentral.x << getChannelTypeScaleX (CH_C, chromaFm), chromaCentral.y << getChannelTypeScaleY (CH_C, chromaFm));
637  const CodingUnit* colLumaCu = bestCS->refCS->getCU (lumaRefPos, CH_L, TREE_D);
638  // update qp
639  qp = colLumaCu->qp;
640  }
641 
642  m_cIntraSearch.reset();
643 
644  bool isReuseCU = m_modeCtrl.isReusingCuValid( cs, partitioner, qp );
645 
646  bool checkIbc = m_pcEncCfg->m_IBCMode && bestCS->picture->useScIBC && (partitioner.chType == CH_L);
647  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_IBCFastMethod>3) && (cs.area.lwidth() * cs.area.lheight()) > (16 * 16))
648  {
649  checkIbc = false;
650  }
651  if( isReuseCU )
652  {
653  xReuseCachedResult( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner );
654  }
655  else
656  {
657  // add first pass modes
658  if ( !slice.isIRAP() && !( cs.area.lwidth() == 4 && cs.area.lheight() == 4 ) && !partitioner.isConsIntra() )
659  {
660  // add inter modes
661  EncTestMode encTestModeSkip = { ETM_MERGE_SKIP, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless };
662  if (m_modeCtrl.tryMode(encTestModeSkip, cs, partitioner))
663  {
664  xCheckRDCostMerge(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestModeSkip);
665 
666  CodingUnit* cu = bestCS->getCU(partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType);
667  if (cu)
668  cu->mmvdSkip = cu->skip == false ? false : cu->mmvdSkip;
669  }
670  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_Geo && cs.slice->isInterB())
671  {
672  EncTestMode encTestModeGeo = { ETM_MERGE_GEO, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless };
673  if (m_modeCtrl.tryMode(encTestModeGeo, cs, partitioner))
674  {
675  xCheckRDCostMergeGeo(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestModeGeo);
676  }
677  }
678  EncTestMode encTestMode = { ETM_INTER_ME, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless };
679  if (m_modeCtrl.tryMode(encTestMode, cs, partitioner))
680  {
681  xCheckRDCostInter(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode);
682  }
683 
684  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_AMVRspeed)
685  {
686  double bestIntPelCost = MAX_DOUBLE;
687 
688  EncTestMode encTestMode = {ETM_INTER_IMV, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless};
689  if( m_modeCtrl.tryMode( encTestMode, cs, partitioner ) )
690  {
691  const bool skipAltHpelIF = ( int( ( encTestMode.opts & ETO_IMV ) >> ETO_IMV_SHIFT ) == 4 ) && ( bestIntPelCost > 1.25 * bestCS->cost );
692  if (!skipAltHpelIF)
693  {
694  tempCS->bestCS = bestCS;
695  xCheckRDCostInterIMV(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
696  tempCS->bestCS = nullptr;
697  }
698  }
699  }
700  }
701  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_EDO && bestCS->cost != MAX_DOUBLE )
702  {
703  xCalDebCost(*bestCS, partitioner);
704  }
705 
706  if (checkIbc && !partitioner.isConsInter())
707  {
708  EncTestMode encTestModeIBCMerge = { ETM_IBC_MERGE, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless };
709  if ((m_pcEncCfg->m_IBCFastMethod < 4) && (partitioner.chType == CH_L) && m_modeCtrl.tryMode(encTestModeIBCMerge, cs, partitioner))
710  {
711  xCheckRDCostIBCModeMerge2Nx2N(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestModeIBCMerge);
712  }
713 
714  EncTestMode encTestModeIBC = { ETM_IBC, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless };
715  if (m_modeCtrl.tryMode(encTestModeIBC, cs, partitioner))
716  {
717  xCheckRDCostIBCMode(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestModeIBC);
718  }
719  }
720 
721  // add intra modes
722  EncTestMode encTestMode( {ETM_INTRA, ETO_STANDARD, qp, lossless} );
723  if( !partitioner.isConsInter() && m_modeCtrl.tryMode( encTestMode, cs, partitioner ) )
724  {
725  xCheckRDCostIntra( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
726  }
727  } // reusing cu
728 
729  m_modeCtrl.beforeSplit( partitioner );
730 
731  if (cuECtx.bestCS && ((cuECtx.bestCostNoImv == (MAX_DOUBLE * .5) || cuECtx.isReusingCu) && !slice.isIntra()) )
732  {
733  m_cInterSearch.loadGlobalUniMvs( lumaArea, *pps.pcv );
734  }
735  } //boundary
736 
738  // split modes
739  EncTestMode lastTestMode;
740 
741  if( cuECtx.qtBeforeBt )
742  {
743  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_QT, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
744  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
745  {
746  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
747  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
748  }
749  }
750 
751  if( partitioner.canSplit( CU_HORZ_SPLIT, cs ) )
752  {
753  // add split modes
754  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_BT_H, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
755  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
756  {
757  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
758  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
759  }
760  }
761 
762  if( partitioner.canSplit( CU_VERT_SPLIT, cs ) )
763  {
764  // add split modes
765  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_BT_V, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
766  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
767  {
768  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
769  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
770  }
771  }
772 
773  if( partitioner.canSplit( CU_TRIH_SPLIT, cs ) )
774  {
775  // add split modes
776  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_TT_H, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
777  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
778  {
779  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
780  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
781  }
782  }
783 
784  if( partitioner.canSplit( CU_TRIV_SPLIT, cs ) )
785  {
786  // add split modes
787  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_TT_V, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
788  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
789  {
790  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
791  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
792  }
793  }
794 
795  if( !cuECtx.qtBeforeBt )
796  {
797  EncTestMode encTestMode( { ETM_SPLIT_QT, ETO_STANDARD, qp, false } );
798  if( m_modeCtrl.trySplit( encTestMode, cs, partitioner, lastTestMode ) )
799  {
800  lastTestMode = encTestMode;
801  xCheckModeSplit( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
802  }
803  }
804  }
805 
806  if( bestCS->cus.empty() )
807  {
808  m_modeCtrl.finishCULevel( partitioner );
809  return;
810  }
811 
813  // Finishing CU
814  // set context states
815  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_CurrCtx->best;
816 
817  // QP from last processed CU for further processing
818  //copy the qp of the last non-chroma CU
819  int numCUInThisNode = (int)bestCS->cus.size();
820  if( numCUInThisNode > 1 && bestCS->cus.back()->chType == CH_C && !CS::isDualITree( *bestCS ) )
821  {
822  CHECK( bestCS->cus[numCUInThisNode-2]->chType != CH_L, "wrong chType" );
823  bestCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->cus[numCUInThisNode-2]->qp;
824  }
825  else
826  {
827  bestCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType] = bestCS->cus.back()->qp;
828  }
829  if ((!slice.isIntra() || slice.sps->IBC)
830  && partitioner.chType == CH_L
831  && bestCS->cus.size() == 1 && (bestCS->cus.back()->predMode == MODE_INTER || bestCS->cus.back()->predMode == MODE_IBC)
832  && bestCS->area.Y() == (*bestCS->cus.back()).Y()
833  )
834  {
835  const CodingUnit& cu = *bestCS->cus.front();
836  bool isIbcSmallBlk = CU::isIBC(cu) && (cu.lwidth() * cu.lheight() <= 16);
837  if (!cu.affine && !cu.geo && !isIbcSmallBlk)
838  {
839  const MotionInfo &mi = cu.getMotionInfo();
840  HPMVInfo hMi( mi, (mi.interDir == 3) ? cu.BcwIdx : BCW_DEFAULT, cu.imv == IMV_HPEL );
841  cu.cs->addMiToLut( CU::isIBC(cu) ? cu.cs->motionLut.lutIbc : cu.cs->motionLut.lut, hMi);
842  }
843  }
844 
845  m_modeCtrl.finishCULevel( partitioner );
846  if( m_cIntraSearch.getSaveCuCostInSCIPU() && bestCS->cus.size() == 1 )
847  {
848  m_cIntraSearch.saveCuAreaCostInSCIPU( Area( partitioner.currArea().lumaPos(), partitioner.currArea().lumaSize() ), bestCS->cost );
849  }
850 
851  // Assert if Best prediction mode is NONE
852  // Selected mode's RD-cost must be not MAX_DOUBLE.
853  CHECK( bestCS->cus.empty() , "No possible encoding found" );
854  CHECK( bestCS->cus[0]->predMode == NUMBER_OF_PREDICTION_MODES, "No possible encoding found" );
855  CHECK( bestCS->cost == MAX_DOUBLE , "No possible encoding found" );
856 }

859 void EncCu::xCheckModeSplit(CodingStructure *&tempCS, CodingStructure *&bestCS, Partitioner &partitioner, const EncTestMode& encTestMode )
860 {
861  const ModeType modeTypeParent = partitioner.modeType;
862  const TreeType treeTypeParent = partitioner.treeType;
863  const ChannelType chTypeParent = partitioner.chType;
864 
865  int signalModeConsVal = tempCS->signalModeCons( getPartSplit( encTestMode ), partitioner, modeTypeParent );
866  int numRoundRdo = signalModeConsVal == LDT_MODE_TYPE_SIGNAL ? 2 : 1;
867  bool skipInterPass = false;
868  for( int i = 0; i < numRoundRdo; i++ )
869  {
870  //change cons modes
871  if( signalModeConsVal == LDT_MODE_TYPE_SIGNAL )
872  {
873  CHECK( numRoundRdo != 2, "numRoundRdo shall be 2 - [LDT_MODE_TYPE_SIGNAL]" );
874  partitioner.modeType = (i == 0) ? MODE_TYPE_INTER : MODE_TYPE_INTRA;
875  }
876  else if( signalModeConsVal == LDT_MODE_TYPE_INFER )
877  {
878  CHECK( numRoundRdo != 1, "numRoundRdo shall be 1 - [LDT_MODE_TYPE_INFER]" );
879  partitioner.modeType = MODE_TYPE_INTRA;
880  }
881  else if( signalModeConsVal == LDT_MODE_TYPE_INHERIT )
882  {
883  CHECK( numRoundRdo != 1, "numRoundRdo shall be 1 - [LDT_MODE_TYPE_INHERIT]" );
884  partitioner.modeType = modeTypeParent;
885  }
886 
887  //for lite intra encoding fast algorithm, set the status to save inter coding info
888  if( modeTypeParent == MODE_TYPE_ALL && partitioner.modeType == MODE_TYPE_INTER )
889  {
890  m_cIntraSearch.setSaveCuCostInSCIPU( true );
891  m_cIntraSearch.setNumCuInSCIPU( 0 );
892  }
893  else if( modeTypeParent == MODE_TYPE_ALL && partitioner.modeType != MODE_TYPE_INTER )
894  {
895  m_cIntraSearch.setSaveCuCostInSCIPU( false );
896  if( partitioner.modeType == MODE_TYPE_ALL )
897  {
898  m_cIntraSearch.setNumCuInSCIPU( 0 );
899  }
900  }
901 
902  xCheckModeSplitInternal( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode, modeTypeParent, skipInterPass );
903  //recover cons modes
904  partitioner.modeType = modeTypeParent;
905  partitioner.treeType = treeTypeParent;
906  partitioner.chType = chTypeParent;
907  if( modeTypeParent == MODE_TYPE_ALL )
908  {
909  m_cIntraSearch.setSaveCuCostInSCIPU( false );
910  if( numRoundRdo == 2 && partitioner.modeType == MODE_TYPE_INTRA )
911  {
912  m_cIntraSearch.initCuAreaCostInSCIPU();
913  }
914  }
915  if( skipInterPass )
916  {
917  break;
918  }
919  }
920 }
921 
922 void EncCu::xCheckModeSplitInternal(CodingStructure *&tempCS, CodingStructure *&bestCS, Partitioner &partitioner, const EncTestMode& encTestMode, const ModeType modeTypeParent, bool& skipInterPass )
923 {
924  const int qp = encTestMode.qp;
925  const int oldPrevQp = tempCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType];
926  const auto oldMotionLut = tempCS->motionLut;
927  const ReshapeData& reshapeData = tempCS->picture->reshapeData;
928 
929  const PartSplit split = getPartSplit( encTestMode );
930  const ModeType modeTypeChild = partitioner.modeType;
931 
932  CHECK( split == CU_DONT_SPLIT, "No proper split provided!" );
933 
934  tempCS->initStructData( qp );
935 
936  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = m_CurrCtx->start;
937 
938  const uint16_t split_ctx_size = Ctx::SplitFlag.size() + Ctx::SplitQtFlag.size() + Ctx::SplitHvFlag.size() + Ctx::Split12Flag.size() + Ctx::ModeConsFlag.size();
939  const TempCtx ctxSplitFlags( m_CtxCache, SubCtx(CtxSet(Ctx::SplitFlag(), split_ctx_size), m_CABACEstimator->getCtx()));
940 
941  m_CABACEstimator->resetBits();
942 
943  m_CABACEstimator->split_cu_mode( split, *tempCS, partitioner );
944  m_CABACEstimator->mode_constraint( split, *tempCS, partitioner, modeTypeChild );
945 
946  int numChild = 3;
947  if( split == CU_VERT_SPLIT || split == CU_HORZ_SPLIT ) numChild--;
948  else if( split == CU_QUAD_SPLIT ) numChild++;
949 
950  int64_t approxBits = m_pcEncCfg->m_qtbttSpeedUp > 0 ? numChild << SCALE_BITS : 0;
951 
952  const double factor = ( tempCS->currQP[partitioner.chType] > 30 ? 1.1 : 1.075 )
953  + ( m_pcEncCfg->m_qtbttSpeedUp > 0 ? 0.01 : 0.0 )
954  + ( ( m_pcEncCfg->m_qtbttSpeedUp > 0 && isChroma( partitioner.chType ) ) ? 0.2 : 0.0 );
955 
956  const double cost = m_cRdCost.calcRdCost( uint64_t( m_CABACEstimator->getEstFracBits() + approxBits + ( ( bestCS->fracBits ) / factor ) ), Distortion( bestCS->dist / factor ) ) + bestCS->costDbOffset / factor;
957 
958  m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = SubCtx(CtxSet(Ctx::SplitFlag(), split_ctx_size), ctxSplitFlags);
959 
960  if (cost > bestCS->cost + bestCS->costDbOffset )
961  {
962 // DTRACE( g_trace_ctx, D_TMP, "%d exit split %f %f %f\n", g_trace_ctx->getChannelCounter(D_TMP), cost, bestCS->cost, bestCS->costDbOffset );
963  xCheckBestMode( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
964  return;
965  }
966 
967  const bool chromaNotSplit = modeTypeParent == MODE_TYPE_ALL && modeTypeChild == MODE_TYPE_INTRA ? true : false;
968 
969  if( partitioner.treeType == TREE_D )
970  {
971  if( chromaNotSplit )
972  {
973  CHECK( partitioner.chType != CH_L, "chType must be luma" );
974  partitioner.treeType = TREE_L;
975  }
976  else
977  {
978  partitioner.treeType = TREE_D;
979  }
980  }
981 
982  CHECK(!(split == CU_QUAD_SPLIT || split == CU_HORZ_SPLIT || split == CU_VERT_SPLIT
983  || split == CU_TRIH_SPLIT || split == CU_TRIV_SPLIT), "invalid split type");
984 
985  partitioner.splitCurrArea( split, *tempCS );
986  bool qgEnableChildren = partitioner.currQgEnable(); // QG possible at children level
987 
988  m_CurrCtx++;
989 
990  AffineMVInfo tmpMVInfo;
991  bool isAffMVInfoSaved = m_cInterSearch.m_AffineProfList->savePrevAffMVInfo(0, tmpMVInfo );
992 
993  BlkUniMvInfo tmpUniMvInfo;
994  bool isUniMvInfoSaved = false;
995  if (!tempCS->slice->isIntra())
996  {
997  m_cInterSearch.m_BlkUniMvInfoBuffer->savePrevUniMvInfo(tempCS->area.Y(), tmpUniMvInfo, isUniMvInfoSaved);
998  }
999 
1000  DeriveCtx deriveCtx = m_CABACEstimator->getDeriveCtx();
1001 
1002  do
1003  {
1004  const auto &subCUArea = partitioner.currArea();
1005 
1006  if( tempCS->picture->Y().contains( subCUArea.lumaPos() ) )
1007  {
1008  PelStorage* orgBuffer = &m_pOrgBuffer[partitioner.currDepth];
1009  PelStorage* rspBuffer = &m_pRspBuffer[partitioner.currDepth];
1010  CodingStructure *tempSubCS = m_pTempCS[partitioner.currDepth];
1011  CodingStructure *bestSubCS = m_pBestCS[partitioner.currDepth];
1012 
1013  tempCS->initSubStructure( *tempSubCS, partitioner.chType, subCUArea, false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
1014  tempCS->initSubStructure( *bestSubCS, partitioner.chType, subCUArea, false, orgBuffer, rspBuffer );
1015 
1016  // copy org buffer, need to be done after initSubStructure because of reshaping!
1017  orgBuffer->copyFrom( tempCS->getOrgBuf( subCUArea ) );
1018  if( tempCS->slice->lmcsEnabled && reshapeData.getCTUFlag() )
1019  {
1020  rspBuffer->Y().copyFrom( tempCS->getRspOrgBuf( subCUArea.Y() ) );
1021  }
1022  m_CABACEstimator->determineNeighborCus( *tempSubCS, partitioner.currArea(), partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType );
1023 
1024  tempSubCS->bestParent = bestSubCS->bestParent = bestCS;
1025 
1026  xCompressCU(tempSubCS, bestSubCS, partitioner );
1027 
1028  tempSubCS->bestParent = bestSubCS->bestParent = nullptr;
1029 
1030  if( bestSubCS->cost == MAX_DOUBLE )
1031  {
1032  CHECK( split == CU_QUAD_SPLIT, "Split decision reusing cannot skip quad split" );
1033  tempCS->cost = MAX_DOUBLE;
1034  tempCS->costDbOffset = 0;
1035  m_CurrCtx--;
1036  partitioner.exitCurrSplit();
1037  xCheckBestMode( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode );
1038  if( partitioner.chType == CH_L )
1039  {
1040  tempCS->motionLut = oldMotionLut;
1041  }
1042 
1043  m_CABACEstimator->getDeriveCtx() = deriveCtx;
1044  return;
1045  }
1046 
1047  tempCS->useSubStructure( *bestSubCS, partitioner.chType, TREE_D, CS::getArea( *tempCS, subCUArea, partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType ), true );
1048 
1049  if( partitioner.currQgEnable() )
1050  {
1051  tempCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType] = bestSubCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType];
1052  }
1053  if( partitioner.isConsInter() )
1054  {
1055  for( int i = 0; i < bestSubCS->cus.size(); i++ )
1056  {
1057  CHECK( bestSubCS->cus[i]->predMode != MODE_INTER, "all CUs must be inter mode in an Inter coding region (SCIPU)" );
1058  }
1059  }
1060  else if( partitioner.isConsIntra() )
1061  {
1062  for( int i = 0; i < bestSubCS->cus.size(); i++ )
1063  {
1064  CHECK( bestSubCS->cus[i]->predMode == MODE_INTER, "all CUs must not be inter mode in an Intra coding region (SCIPU)" );
1065  }
1066  }
1067 
1068  tempSubCS->releaseIntermediateData();
1069  bestSubCS->releaseIntermediateData();
1070  if( !tempCS->slice->isIntra() && partitioner.isConsIntra() )
1071  {
1072  tempCS->cost = m_cRdCost.calcRdCost( tempCS->fracBits, tempCS->dist );
1073  if( tempCS->cost > bestCS->cost )
1074  {
1075  tempCS->cost = MAX_DOUBLE;
1076  tempCS->costDbOffset = 0;
1077  m_CurrCtx--;
1078  partitioner.exitCurrSplit();
1079  if( partitioner.chType == CH_L )
1080  {
1081  tempCS->motionLut = oldMotionLut;
1082  }
1083 
1084  m_CABACEstimator->getDeriveCtx() = deriveCtx;
1085  return;
1086  }
1087  }
1088  }
1089  } while( partitioner.nextPart( *tempCS ) );
1090 
1091  partitioner.exitCurrSplit();
1092 
1093  m_CurrCtx--;
1094 
1095  m_CABACEstimator->getDeriveCtx() = deriveCtx;
1096 
1097  if( chromaNotSplit )
1098  {
1099  //Note: In local dual tree region, the chroma CU refers to the central luma CU's QP.
1100  //If the luma CU QP shall be predQP (no residual in it and before it in the QG), it must be revised to predQP before encoding the chroma CU
1101  //Otherwise, the chroma CU uses predQP+deltaQP in encoding but is decoded as using predQP, thus causing encoder-decoded mismatch on chroma qp.
1102  if( tempCS->pps->useDQP )
1103  {
1104  //find parent CS that including all coded CUs in the QG before this node
1105  CodingStructure* qgCS = tempCS;
1106  bool deltaQpCodedBeforeThisNode = false;
1107  if( partitioner.currArea().lumaPos() != partitioner.currQgPos )
1108  {
1109  int numParentNodeToQgCS = 0;
1110  while( qgCS->area.lumaPos() != partitioner.currQgPos )
1111  {
1112  CHECK( qgCS->parent == nullptr, "parent of qgCS shall exsit" );
1113  qgCS = qgCS->parent;
1114  numParentNodeToQgCS++;
1115  }
1116 
1117  //check whether deltaQP has been coded (in luma CU or luma&chroma CU) before this node
1118  CodingStructure* parentCS = tempCS->parent;
1119  for( int i = 0; i < numParentNodeToQgCS; i++ )
1120  {
1121  //checking each parent
1122  CHECK( parentCS == nullptr, "parentCS shall exsit" );
1123  for( const auto &cu : parentCS->cus )
1124  {
1125  if( cu->rootCbf && !isChroma( cu->chType ) )
1126  {
1127  deltaQpCodedBeforeThisNode = true;
1128  break;
1129  }
1130  }
1131  parentCS = parentCS->parent;
1132  }
1133  }
1134 
1135  //revise luma CU qp before the first luma CU with residual in the SCIPU to predQP
1136  if( !deltaQpCodedBeforeThisNode )
1137  {
1138  //get pred QP of the QG
1139  const CodingUnit* cuFirst = qgCS->getCU( CH_L, TREE_D );
1140  CHECK( cuFirst->lumaPos() != partitioner.currQgPos, "First cu of the Qg is wrong" );
1141  int predQp = CU::predictQP( *cuFirst, qgCS->prevQP[CH_L] );
1142 
1143  //revise to predQP
1144  int firstCuHasResidual = (int)tempCS->cus.size();
1145  for( int i = 0; i < tempCS->cus.size(); i++ )
1146  {
1147  if( tempCS->cus[i]->rootCbf )
1148  {
1149  firstCuHasResidual = i;
1150  break;
1151  }
1152  }
1153 
1154  for( int i = 0; i < firstCuHasResidual; i++ )
1155  {
1156  tempCS->cus[i]->qp = predQp;
1157  }
1158  }
1159  }
1160  partitioner.chType = CH_C;
1161  partitioner.treeType = TREE_C;
1162 
1163  m_CurrCtx++;
1164 
1165  CodingStructure *tempCSChroma = m_pTempCS2;
1166  CodingStructure *bestCSChroma = m_pBestCS2;
1167 
1168  tempCS->initSubStructure( *tempCSChroma, partitioner.chType, partitioner.currArea(), false );
1169  tempCS->initSubStructure( *bestCSChroma, partitioner.chType, partitioner.currArea(), false );
1170  m_CABACEstimator->determineNeighborCus( *bestCSChroma, partitioner.currArea(), partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType );
1171  tempCSChroma->refCS = tempCS;
1172  bestCSChroma->refCS = tempCS;
1173  xCompressCU( tempCSChroma, bestCSChroma, partitioner );
1174 
1175  //attach chromaCS to luma CS and update cost
1176  tempCS->useSubStructure( *bestCSChroma, partitioner.chType, TREE_D, CS::getArea( *bestCSChroma, partitioner.currArea(), partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType ), true );
1177 
1178  //release tmp resource
1179  tempCSChroma->releaseIntermediateData();
1180  bestCSChroma->releaseIntermediateData();
1181 
1182  m_CurrCtx--;
1183  //recover luma tree status
1184  partitioner.chType = CH_L;
1185  partitioner.treeType = TREE_D;
1186  partitioner.modeType = MODE_TYPE_ALL;
1187  }
1188 
1189  // Finally, generate split-signaling bits for RD-cost check
1190  const PartSplit implicitSplit = partitioner.getImplicitSplit( *tempCS );
1191 
1192  {
1193  bool enforceQT = implicitSplit == CU_QUAD_SPLIT;
1194 
1195  // LARGE CTU bug
1196  if( m_pcEncCfg->m_useFastLCTU )
1197  {
1198  unsigned minDepth = m_modeCtrl.comprCUCtx->minDepth;
1199  if( minDepth > partitioner.currQtDepth )
1200  {
1201  // enforce QT
1202  enforceQT = true;
1203  }
1204  }
1205 
1206  if( !enforceQT )
1207  {
1208  m_CABACEstimator->resetBits();
1209 
1210  m_CABACEstimator->split_cu_mode( split, *tempCS, partitioner );
1211  partitioner.modeType = modeTypeParent;
1212  m_CABACEstimator->mode_constraint( split, *tempCS, partitioner, modeTypeChild );
1213  tempCS->fracBits += m_CABACEstimator->getEstFracBits(); // split bits
1214  }
1215  }
1216 
1217  tempCS->cost = m_cRdCost.calcRdCost( tempCS->fracBits, tempCS->dist );
1218 
1219  // Check Delta QP bits for splitted structure
1220  if( !qgEnableChildren ) // check at deepest QG level only
1221  xCheckDQP( *tempCS, partitioner, true );
1222 
1223  // If the configuration being tested exceeds the maximum number of bytes for a slice / slice-segment, then
1224  // a proper RD evaluation cannot be performed. Therefore, termination of the
1225  // slice/slice-segment must be made prior to this CTU.
1226  // This can be achieved by forcing the decision to be that of the rpcTempCU.
1227  // The exception is each slice / slice-segment must have at least one CTU.
1228  if (bestCS->cost == MAX_DOUBLE)
1229  {
1230  bestCS->costDbOffset = 0;
1231  }
1232 
1233  if( tempCS->cus.size() > 0 && modeTypeParent == MODE_TYPE_ALL && modeTypeChild == MODE_TYPE_INTER )
1234  {
1235  int areaSizeNoResiCu = 0;
1236  for( int k = 0; k < tempCS->cus.size(); k++ )
1237  {
1238  areaSizeNoResiCu += (tempCS->cus[k]->rootCbf == false) ? tempCS->cus[k]->lumaSize().area() : 0;
1239  }
1240  if( areaSizeNoResiCu >= (tempCS->area.lumaSize().area() >> 1) )
1241  {
1242  skipInterPass = true;
1243  }
1244  }
1245 
1246  // RD check for sub partitioned coding structure.
1247  xCheckBestMode( tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode, m_pcEncCfg->m_EDO );
1248 
1249  if( isAffMVInfoSaved)
1250  {
1251  m_cInterSearch.m_AffineProfList->addAffMVInfo(tmpMVInfo);
1252  }
1253 
1254  if (!tempCS->slice->isIntra() && isUniMvInfoSaved)
1255  {
1256  m_cInterSearch.m_BlkUniMvInfoBuffer->addUniMvInfo(tmpUniMvInfo);
1257  }
1258 
1259  tempCS->motionLut = oldMotionLut;
1260  tempCS->releaseIntermediateData();
1261  tempCS->prevQP[partitioner.chType] = oldPrevQp;
1262 }

1301  {

1307  bestMode |= neigh->lfnstIdx ? 2 : 0;
1308  bestMode |= neigh->ispMode ? 1 : 0;
1309  m_cIntraSearch.m_ispTestedModes[0].bestBefore[i+1] = bestMode;
1310  }
1311  }
1312  }
1313  }
1314 
1315  tempCS->interHad = m_modeCtrl.comprCUCtx->interHad;
1316  double maxCostAllowedForChroma = MAX_DOUBLE;
1317  if( isLuma( partitioner.chType ) )
1318  {
1319  if (!tempCS->slice->isIntra() && bestCS)
1320  {
1321  m_cIntraSearch.estIntraPredLumaQT(cu, partitioner, bestCS->cost);
1322  }
1323  else
1324  {
1325  m_cIntraSearch.estIntraPredLumaQT(cu, partitioner);
1326  }
1327  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_FastIntraTools)
1328  {
1329  m_modeCtrl.comprCUCtx->bestIntraMode = m_cIntraSearch.m_ispTestedModes[0].bestIntraMode;

1331  {

1333  }
1334  }
1335 
1336  if( !partitioner.isSepTree( *tempCS ) )

1339  }
1340  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_usePbIntraFast && tempCS->dist == MAX_DISTORTION && tempCS->interHad == 0)
1341  {
1342  // JEM assumes only perfect reconstructions can from now on beat the inter mode
1343  m_modeCtrl.comprCUCtx->interHad = 0;
1344  return;
1345  }
1346  }
1347 
1348  if( tempCS->area.chromaFormat != CHROMA_400 && ( partitioner.chType == CH_C || !CU::isSepTree(cu) ) )
1349  {

1355  }

1357  cu, (!useIntraSubPartitions || (CU::isSepTree(cu) && !isLuma(CH_C))) ? partitioner : subTuPartitioner,
1358  maxCostAllowedForChroma);

1362  }

1366

1368  {
1369  cu.rootCbf |= cu.firstTU->cbf[t] != 0;
1370  }
1371 
1372  // Get total bits for current mode: encode CU
1373  m_CABACEstimator->resetBits();
1374 
1375  if ((!cu.cs->slice->isIntra() || cu.cs->slice->sps->IBC) && cu.Y().valid())

1388  tempCS->fracBits = m_CABACEstimator->getEstFracBits();

1390 
1391  xEncodeDontSplit(*tempCS, partitioner);
1392 
1393  xCheckDQP(*tempCS, partitioner);
1394 
1395  if (m_pcEncCfg->m_EDO)
1396  {

1400  DTRACE_MODE_COST(*tempCS, m_cRdCost.getLambda(true));
1401  xCheckBestMode(tempCS, bestCS, partitioner, encTestMode, m_pcEncCfg->m_EDO);
1402 
1403  STAT_COUNT_CU_MODES( partitioner.chType == CH_L, g_cuCounters1D[CU_MODES_TESTED][0][!tempCS->slice->isIntra() + tempCS->slice->depth] );
1404  STAT_COUNT_CU_MODES( partitioner.chType == CH_L && !tempCS->slice->isIntra(), g_cuCounters2D[CU_MODES_TESTED][Log2( tempCS->area.lheight() )][Log2( tempCS->area.lwidth() )] );
1405 }

1425 void EncCu::xCheckDQP( CodingStructure& cs, Partitioner& partitioner, bool bKeepCtx )
1426 {
1427  if( !cs.pps->useDQP )
1428  {
1429  return;
1430  }
1431 
1432  if (partitioner.isSepTree(cs) && isChroma(partitioner.chType))
1433  {
1434  return;
1435  }
1436 
1437  if( !partitioner.currQgEnable() ) // do not consider split or leaf/not leaf QG condition (checked by caller)
1438  {
1439  return;
1440  }
1441 
1442  CodingUnit* cuFirst = cs.getCU( partitioner.chType, partitioner.treeType );
1443 
1444  CHECK( bKeepCtx && cs.cus.size() <= 1 && partitioner.getImplicitSplit( cs ) == CU_DONT_SPLIT, "bKeepCtx should only be set in split case" );
1445  CHECK( !bKeepCtx && cs.cus.size() > 1, "bKeepCtx should never be set for non-split case" );
1446  CHECK( !cuFirst, "No CU available" );
1447 
1448  bool hasResidual = false;
1449  for( const auto &cu : cs.cus )
1450  {
1451  //not include the chroma CU because chroma CU is decided based on corresponding luma QP and deltaQP is not signaled at chroma CU
1452  if( cu->rootCbf && !isChroma( cu->chType ))
1453  {
1454  hasResidual = true;
1455  break;
1456  }
1457  }
1458 
1459  int predQP = CU::predictQP( *cuFirst, cs.prevQP[partitioner.chType] );
1460 
1461  if( hasResidual )
1462  {
1463  TempCtx ctxTemp( m_CtxCache );
1464  if( !bKeepCtx ) ctxTemp = SubCtx( Ctx::DeltaQP, m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() );
1465 
1466  m_CABACEstimator->resetBits();
1467  m_CABACEstimator->cu_qp_delta( *cuFirst, predQP, cuFirst->qp );
1468 
1469  cs.fracBits += m_CABACEstimator->getEstFracBits(); // dQP bits
1470  cs.cost = m_cRdCost.calcRdCost(cs.fracBits, cs.dist);
1471 
1472 
1473  if( !bKeepCtx ) m_CABACEstimator->getCtx() = SubCtx( Ctx::DeltaQP, ctxTemp );
1474 
1475  // NOTE: reset QPs for CUs without residuals up to first coded CU
1476  for( const auto &cu : cs.cus )
1477  {
1478  //not include the chroma CU because chroma CU is decided based on corresponding luma QP and deltaQP is not signaled at chroma CU
1479  if( cu->rootCbf && !isChroma( cu->chType ))
1480  {
1481  break;
1482  }
1483  cu->qp = predQP;
1484  }
1485  }
1486  else
1487  {
1488  // No residuals: reset CU QP to predicted value
1489  for( const auto &cu : cs.cus )
1490  {
1491  cu->qp = predQP;
1492  }
1493  }
1494 }

1496 void EncCu::xCheckRDCostMerge( CodingStructure *&tempCS, CodingStructure *&bestCS, Partitioner &partitioner, EncTestMode& encTestMode )
1497 {
1498  PROFILER_SCOPE_AND_STAGE_EXT( 1, g_timeProfiler, P_INTER_MRG, tempCS, partitioner.chType );
1499  const Slice &slice = *tempCS->slice;
1500  const SPS& sps = *tempCS->sps;
1501 
1502  CHECK( slice.sliceType == VVENC_I_SLICE, "Merge modes not available for I-slices" );
1503 
1504  tempCS->initStructData( encTestMode.qp );
1505 
1506  MergeCtx mergeCtx;
1507  bool affineMrgAvail =!((m_pcEncCfg->m_Affine > 1) && (bestCS->slice->TLayer > 3) && (!m_pcEncCfg->m_SbTMVP))
1508  && (m_pcEncCfg->m_Affine || sps.SbtMvp) && m_pcEncCfg->m_maxNumAffineMergeCand
1509  && !(bestCS->area.lumaSize().width < 8 || bestCS->area.lumaSize().height < 8);
1510 
1511  AffineMergeCtx affineMergeCtx;
1512  MergeCtx mrgCtx;
1513

3487 bool checkValidMvs( const CodingUnit& cu)
3488 {
3489  // clang-format off
3490  const int affineShiftTab[3] =
3491  {
3492  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_QUARTER,
3493  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_SIXTEENTH,
3494  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_INT
3495  };
3496 
3497  const int normalShiftTab[NUM_IMV_MODES] =
3498  {
3499  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_QUARTER,
3500  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_INT,
3501  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_4PEL,
3502  MV_PRECISION_INTERNAL - MV_PRECISION_HALF,
3503  };
3504  // clang-format on
3505 
3506  int mvShift;
3507 
3508  for (int refList = 0; refList < NUM_REF_PIC_LIST_01; refList++)
3509  {
3510  if (cu.refIdx[refList] >= 0)
3511  {
3512  if (!cu.affine)
3513  {
3514  mvShift = normalShiftTab[cu.imv];
3515  Mv signaledmvd(cu.mvd[refList][0].hor >> mvShift, cu.mvd[refList][0].ver >> mvShift);
3516  if (!((signaledmvd.hor >= MVD_MIN) && (signaledmvd.hor <= MVD_MAX)) || !((signaledmvd.ver >= MVD_MIN) && (signaledmvd.ver <= MVD_MAX)))
3517  return false;
3518  }
3519  else
3520  {
3521  for (int ctrlP = 1 + (cu.affineType == AFFINEMODEL_6PARAM); ctrlP >= 0; ctrlP--)
3522  {
3523  mvShift = affineShiftTab[cu.imv];
3524  Mv signaledmvd(cu.mvd[refList][ctrlP].hor >> mvShift, cu.mvd[refList][ctrlP].ver >> mvShift);
3525  if (!((signaledmvd.hor >= MVD_MIN) && (signaledmvd.hor <= MVD_MAX)) || !((signaledmvd.ver >= MVD_MIN) && (signaledmvd.ver <= MVD_MAX)))
3526  return false;;
3527  }
3528  }
3529  }
3530  }
3531  // avoid MV exceeding 18-bit dynamic range
3532  const int maxMv = 1 << 17;
3533  if (!cu.affine && !cu.mergeFlag)
3534  {
3535  if ((cu.refIdx[0] >= 0 && (cu.mv[0][0].getAbsHor() >= maxMv || cu.mv[0][0].getAbsVer() >= maxMv))
3536  || (cu.refIdx[1] >= 0 && (cu.mv[1][0].getAbsHor() >= maxMv || cu.mv[1][0].getAbsVer() >= maxMv)))
3537  {
3538  return false;
3539  }
3540  }
3541  if (cu.affine && !cu.mergeFlag)
3542  {
3543  for (int refList = 0; refList < NUM_REF_PIC_LIST_01; refList++)
3544  {
3545  if (cu.refIdx[refList] >= 0)
3546  {
3547  for (int ctrlP = 1 + (cu.affineType == AFFINEMODEL_6PARAM); ctrlP >= 0; ctrlP--)
3548  {
3549  if (cu.mv[refList][ctrlP].getAbsHor() >= maxMv || cu.mv[refList][ctrlP].getAbsVer() >= maxMv)
3550  {
3551  return false;
3552  }
3553  }
3554  }
3555  }
3556  }
3557  return true;
3558 }
